Firstly the course explains the main principles and methods of modern taxonomy and classification. Second, the course gives an holistic overview on the nature and evolution of eukaryotic organisms at a super-group level. We introduce main types of life-forms, life-history, life-cycles, and ecological role of main protist and fungal taxa.Objectives/eesmärkid:  An introduction to the emergence of eukaryotes and the main groups of protists and fungi.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student will get a conceptual understanding of the evolutionary diversity of eukaryotes. Main groups of eukaryotic micro-organisms - protists and fungi will be delalt in more detail, including life cycles, life forms, habitats and ecology.
